The Python companion follows the established RECIPE-GUIDE.md structure and matches the voice and quality of [38;5;10mchapter11.01-python-example.md[0m. It maps 1:1 to the ten pseudocode steps from the main recipe:[0m[0m
[0m[0m
1. [1mReceive message and bootstrap session[22m with greeting, disclosure, and input safety screening (crisis detection, prompt-injection detection, PHI minimization)[0m[0m
2. [1mClassify intent[22m with the small-model classifier and route to in-scope scheduling flow or out-of-scope handoff[0m[0m
3. [1mVerify identity[22m at the assurance level the intent and channel require, with graduated step-up[0m[0m
4. [1mSearch for slots[22m with visit-type mapping from natural-language reason for visit, plus high-acuity clinical-content backstop[0m[0m
5. [1mRefine or select[22m through conversation with slot hold (the search-then-hold-then-confirm-then-book transactional contract)[0m[0m
6. [1mConfirm booking[22m with explicit confirmation, journal write, and event emission[0m[0m
7. [1mHandle reschedule and cancel[22m through appointment lookup, policy checks, and step-up auth for same-day actions[0m[0m
8. [1mHandle booking failures[22m (slot races, system errors, policy violations, duplicate bookings) without losing patient trust[0m[0m
9. [1mOutput safety screening[22m with the scheduling-specific booking-claim verification check (every "your appointment is confirmed" claim must be backed by a successful [38;5;10mslot_book[0m ledger entry)[0m[0m
10. [1mClose conversation and archive[22m with the durable audit record, tool-call ledger, and booking-event journal[0m[0m
[0m[0m
The file also includes a tool-surface section ([38;5;10mpatient_lookup_tool[0m, [38;5;10mslot_search_tool[0m, [38;5;10mslot_hold_tool[0m, [38;5;10mslot_book_tool[0m, [38;5;10mslot_cancel_tool[0m, [38;5;10mappointment_lookup_tool[0m), full mocks ([38;5;10mMockSchedulingSystem[0m, [38;5;10mMockBedrockRuntime[0m, [38;5;10mMockTable[0m, etc.), a [38;5;10mrun_demo()[0m runner exercising five scenarios (happy-path booking, high-acuity routing, refill handoff, cancellation through authenticated portal embed, prompt-injection block), and a thorough "Gap Between This and Production" section.[0m[0m
